<br>
The young Amazon had come to pay her respects to the great shamaness who had aided her in the claiming of her soon-to-be lands.  She stood amongst a large crowd of Amazons who, to, wanted to see Yakut.  She released her mare's reigns, and her horse knew where to go without guidance.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yakut!  Yakut!&quot; She stepped towards the woman and noticed the great change in her appearance.  Her trademark smile of cynicism fell across her lips as sarcastic thoughts filled her head.  Suddenly she raised her voice louder, &quot;Hey, Yakut!  You old crone!&quot;  Laughter played her voice when she called her aged friend. <p>Ø×××|¯A_m¯a_r¯i_c¯e_&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonqueenyakut>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen Shamaness</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/03 4:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/magickalamzn/images/yakut1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..Amarice? o.O O.O !!!</span><hr size=1> Yakut took the seat by the fire as offered, but only moments after she sat down a familiar voice called out to her. The Queen turned her head and her green orbs fell upon Amarice. She quickly got to her feet, kissed her daughter on her forehead, and with arms open ran towards Amarice. She charged and tackled the young Amazon down to the ground. She looked down at Amarice's face with a playful smile on her face.<br>
<br>
&quot;I maybe old, but I can still run with the young of them.&quot;, she chuckled and got to her feet. The Amazon stretched out her arm and helped Amarice to her feet.<br>
<br>
&quot;How've you been, Amarice? How does Samos fair as well?&quot;, she had hoped that Amarice's lands had prospered as hers. If not, Yakut would send her best workers and herself to help out. <p>-|-Queen Yakut-|-<br>
-Shamaness of the Old Ways-<br>
&quot;Just as daughter becomes mother, the student becomes the teacher. Their strength will be their unity. Their courage will be their guide.&quot;-Yakut</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swordofyouth>Sword of Youth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/03 7:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/darkmoonhex/images/amarice.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yakut! &gt;&lt;</span><hr size=1> Before she could even blink, the old shamaness struck her to the ground with all of her body weight.  A loud grunt was forced from her lungs because of the impact, as she was slammed against the ground.  When the tackle was over, Amarice began to laugh.  But suddenly, she ended her laughter and brought her features into a glare upon Yakut.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ohh..you obviously don't get enough running.  You're heavy as a horse, you old hag!&quot;  She placed her pale, slinder fingers across Yakut's shoulders and attempted to push her off.<br>
<br>
When Yakut was to her feet and offered Amarice help, she had to show some kind of respect...so she took her hand.  When she was to her feet, Amarice brushed off some of the dirt that had managed to collect onto her leathers, and brought her hazel orbs back onto Yakut.<br>
<br>
&quot;Samos...well...it's empty.  It's slightly hard getting a tribe off, which I am sure you know.  I hope you'll be able to drop by again.&quot;<br>
<br>
She eyed Yakut down once more before she brought the shamaness into an embrace.  Amarice lowered her voice and this time as she whispered to Yakut, her voice was full of sincerety instead of sarcasm.<br>
<br>
&quot;I've missed you, Yakut.  I am so glad you've returned.&quot; <p>Ø×××|¯A_m¯a_r¯i_c¯e_&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amznnye>AmznNye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/03 9:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Crazy? maybe not....</span><hr size=1> She smiled at Otere's reassurance of her lack of insanity. &quot;I'm glad I came as well...I haven't met very many people since coming to any of the Amazon lands.&quot; She glanced over at the going's on between Yakut and the younger woman, smiling a bit to herself, then looked back to Otere. &quot;Maybe...if you wouldn't mind too much...you could show me around?&quot; She couldn't help the hopeful little glitter that flashed through her blue-green eyes then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otereshamaness>OtereShamaness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/03 11:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.members.aol.com/darkmoonhex/images/otere.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crazy? maybe not....</span><hr size=1> Otere titled her head to the side when Nye spoke a bit of her past.  She loved learning about people's past, and wanted to learn her's.  Her auburn occulars caught a glimpse of the commotion between Yakut and Amarice, a giggled a bit at the two, but quickly returned her attention to Nye when she began to speak again.<br>
